items.title: Live: Can Nifty Defend 24,000 As Technical Bounce Reverses? Tata Motors In Focus | Opening Bell
items.description: Indian equity market continued its consolidation for another week, slipping over half a percent, indicating an ongoing corrective phase. The week started cautiously, with investor sentiment dampened by concerns around the upcoming US Presidential elections. A brief mid-week rally followed the election results, but gains were short-lived, as volatility persisted amid various global events. As we move into the second week of November, investors will keep a close eye on several critical factors, including the final set of Q2FY25 earnings, geopolitical tensions in the Middle East, FII flows, crude oil prices, global market trends, and key domestic and international macroeconomic data. On Wall Street, Trump-fuelled rally continued unabated with Dow toppling 44,000 for the first time and the S&P 500 ending at record high to cap election week rally. Among stocks to watch out for today will be SBI, as brokerages spell out their verdict on the stock post quarterly earnings, M&M, Asian Paints, LIC. Catch Nandita Khemka in conversation with Ajit Mishra - SVP, Research, Religare Broking and market expert Prakash Diwan

items.title: KEC International|  Debt Reduction, strong execution, and robust Order Book to drive Growth Outlook
items.description: KEC International has achieved notable growth, cementing its leadership in the T&D sector and expanding into railways, solar, and civil engineering. In Q2FY25, the company saw strong revenue growth with a 6.26% EBITDA margin. The company is expecting closer to Rs 25000 crore inflows this year. Now with an order book of Rs 34,088 crore, KEC's growth outlook is solid. Strategic moves like cable business monetization and debt reduction would only boost its investment appeal.
